# fold

> Display content of files wrapped
> Help: --help
> Version: --version
> See also: fmt, pr
> More information: https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/fold

- Display content of specific files with lines wrapped at 80 characters:

`fold {/?file+ file: ~/.bashrc}`

- Display content of files with lines wrapped at specific character count:

`fold {option width: --width, -w} {int width: 30} {/?file+ file: ~/.bashrc}`

- Display content of specific files with lines wrapped at word boundaries:

`fold {option enable wrapping at word boundaries: --spaces, -s} {/?file+ file: ~/.bashrc}`
